    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - PRINCIPLES, OPERATION AND SERVICE - INSTALL - FRONT SENSOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FRONT SENSOR</title>
        <para>Install the sensor into the retainer and sensor bushing from the backside of the steering knuckle. Push
            the sensor as far as possible through the sensor bushing. Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0402907">Figure 7</hotlnk>. No further adjustment is necessary.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0402907" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0402907" filename="../figg04/G0402907.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Installing Front Sensor</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SENSOR BUSHING (PART OF KNUCKLE ASSY)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SENSOR RETAINER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SENSOR RETAINER OUTSIDE TONGUES</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SENSOR ASSEMBLY INCLUDES LEAD (CONNECTS TO CHASSIS ANTILOCK HARNESS)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. STEERING KNUCKLE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. FRONT CHAMBER SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
